  // Dance Classes Hub - What to Expect Section
  danceClassesHub_whatToExpect_title: 'What will you find in our dance classes in Barcelona?',
  danceClassesHub_whatToExpect_p1:
    "At Farray's International Dance Center we offer over 30 different dance styles: from classical Cuban School technique (classical ballet, afro contemporary, afro jazz) to the most explosive urban dances of the moment (dancehall, k-pop, twerk, commercial dance), through Latin partner dances (Cuban salsa, bachata, timba) and specific physical training for dancers. Each style is designed for you to discover your passion and develop your skills from day one.",
  danceClassesHub_whatToExpect_p2:
    "We organize all our groups by real levels: initiation (never danced before), intermediate (basic experience) and advanced (technique mastery). Absolute beginners are more than welcome: our initiation classes are designed to make you feel comfortable from minute one, without pressure, with clear progression and in a motivating environment. It doesn't matter if you've never danced: your journey starts here.",
  danceClassesHub_whatToExpect_p3:
    'We are located in the heart of Barcelona, near Plaça Catalunya and with direct access from Metro L1 and L2. Our school is easily accessible from the neighborhoods of Raval, Eixample, Gràcia, Sant Antoni, Ciutat Vella and the entire metropolitan area. Flexible schedules in morning, afternoon and weekends so you can find the class that best fits your schedule.',
  danceClassesHub_whatToExpect_p4:
    "Our teaching team consists of professional dancers trained at Cuba's National School of Arts, with careers in international companies and real pedagogical experience. They don't just master the technique: they know how to transmit it with passion, patience and a method that works. You'll learn from the best in a family-like, professional and vibrant environment that will make you feel part of our community from day one.",

