  // Dance Classes Hub - Why FIDC Section
  danceClassesHub_why_title:
    "Why choose the dance classes at Farray's International Dance Center Barcelona?",
  danceClassesHub_why_subtitle:
    'We are much more than a dance school. We are a professional space where technique, passion and quality combine to offer you the best learning experience.',

  danceClassesHub_why_variety_title: '30+ styles under one roof',
  danceClassesHub_why_variety_content:
    'The most complete dance school in Barcelona. From Cuban classical ballet to k-pop, dancehall, salsa, bachata, twerk, pilates and much more. Everything in one place, no need to go to multiple academies. Discover your style or combine several: here you have access to the entire universe of dance.',

  danceClassesHub_why_farray_method_title: 'Farray Method®',
  danceClassesHub_why_farray_method_content:
    'Exclusive teaching system created by Yunaisy Farray, Street Dance 2 dancer and internationally recognized master. Combines technical rigor with creativity for fast and solid results in all dance styles: from classical dance to urban and Latin.',

  danceClassesHub_why_cuban_title: 'Teachers with professional Cuban training',
  danceClassesHub_why_cuban_content:
    "A large part of our teaching team is trained in prestigious dance schools in Cuba, recognized worldwide for their technical excellence. You'll learn with teachers who master the Cuban methodology in ballet, contemporary, folklore, salsa and other disciplines. Solid technique, unique expressiveness and professional rigor.",

  danceClassesHub_why_levels_title: 'Groups by real levels (no mixing)',
  danceClassesHub_why_levels_content:
    "We don't mix beginners with advanced students. Each group is organized by real level: initiation, intermediate, advanced. You'll progress at your own pace, without frustrations, with classmates of your same level. Periodic evaluations to ensure you're always in the right group and evolve constantly.",

  danceClassesHub_why_location_title: 'Central location in the heart of Barcelona',
  danceClassesHub_why_location_content:
    'At Carrer de Floridablanca 135, near Plaça Espanya and Sants Station. Easily accessible by metro, bus or on foot from Raval, Eixample, Gràcia, Sant Antoni, Ciutat Vella and the entire metropolitan area. Professional facilities, spacious rooms with dance floor, mirrors and inspiring atmosphere.',

  danceClassesHub_why_schedule_title: 'Flexible schedules from Monday to Sunday',
  danceClassesHub_why_schedule_content:
    'Morning, afternoon and evening classes adapted to your routine. Schedules from Monday to Sunday so you can find the perfect time according to your availability. Multiple weekly classes of each style allow you to progress quickly. Check our complete schedule and find your ideal time.',

  danceClassesHub_why_accreditation_title: 'School accredited by CID-UNESCO',
  danceClassesHub_why_accreditation_content:
    'We are official members of the International Dance Council (CID-UNESCO), an organization that brings together the best dance schools and professionals in the world. This accreditation guarantees the quality of our teaching, the rigor of our methodology and the international recognition of your training.',

